Key Match Events: Tim Pringle was bowled by Taskin Ahmed for 1 run.
Taskin Ahmed took the wicket of Tim Pringle in the final over.
Pre-Game Insights: Bangladesh and Netherlands hoped for better batting conditions in Kingstown after struggling in New York.
Bangladesh endured a hectic travel schedule with a delayed flight and cancelled training.
Bangladesh's top order batting has been worrying, with no double-digit stands yet in the tournament.
Netherlands have bowled well in the T20 World Cup, beating Nepal and pushing South Africa close.
Logan van Beek has been Netherlands' best bowler, picking up five wickets in two matches.
Miscellaneous Highlights: International cricket returned to Arnos Vale after nearly ten years.
Bangladesh played the last international match at Arnos Vale in 2014.
Bangladesh hold a 4-3 win record over Netherlands in all formats but lost their most recent meeting in the 2023 World Cup.
